Package com.imaginea.mongodb.requestdispatchers

Class Summary
BaseRequestDispatcher Defines validation functions for validating tokenId given to user.
CollectionRequestDispatcher Defines resources for performing create/drop operations on collections present inside databases in Mongo we are currently connected to.
DatabaseRequestDispatcher Defines resources for performing create/drop operations on databases present in Mongo we are currently connected to.
DocumentRequestDispatcher Defines resources for performing create/delete/update operations on documents present inside collections in databases in Mongo we are currently connected to.
Graphs Return values of queries,updates,inserts and deletes being performed on Mongo Db per sec.
StatisticsRequestDispatcher Defines resources for getting statistics of mongo Server and statistics of a particualr database present in mongo and statistics of a collection present inside a database.
TroubleShoot Defines a Servlet to perform troubleshoot operations.
UserLogin Authenticates User to Mongo Db by checking the user in collection of admin database.
UserLogout Listens at a logout Request made by the user and destroys user id from the the mappings in UserLogin class and also from the session.
